This paper focuses on incentive mechanism design for cache-assisted D2D communications, which involves network optimization, game theory, and information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves game theory, which suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as a likely category. Additionally, the paper involves optimization, which suggests cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IT (Information Theory) as possible categories. Finally, the paper involves mobile networks, which suggests cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as a possible category.
